abstract: >-
  BioEval is a multi-dimensional evaluation benchmark for large language models
  in biological research. It measures capabilities beyond factual recall,
  including protocol reasoning, lab calculations, troubleshooting, causal
  biology, experimental design evaluation, calibration, and adversarial
  robustness. The benchmark contains 696 evaluation items (296 base + 400
  extended) across 12 assessment components.
